article.headline: Fordham 86, Duquesne 83
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Bryant Dunston's two free throws broke an 82-82 tie with 1:35 to play and Fordham held on for an 86-83 victory over Duquesne to snap a four-game losing streak Sunday. Reggie Jackson of the Dukes (10-14, 6-7 Atlantic 10) had hit a pair of foul shots with 1:55 remaining to tie the score 82-82. Following Dunston's game-deciding foul shots, Robert Mitchell made the front end of a two-shot foul to get the visitors to within 84-83 with 37 seconds remaining. Michael Binns of the Rams then stole the ball, was found Kieron Achara with eight seconds left and hit both free throws to clinch the victory. Brenton Butler had 28 points for Fordham (14-11, 7-6). Dunston added 19 and Marcus Stout 16. Achara's 20 points paced the Dukes, who trailed 47-44 at the half. Mitchell had 16 and Scott Grote 13.
